The most common way would be to use a grid for that:

```typ
#set page(
  header: {
    grid(
      // this grid fills the whole width of the header
      columns: (1fr, 1fr),
      // the left and right content are aligned correctly
      align: (left, right),
      [left],
      [right],
      // under the first and only row, there's a line
      grid.hline(),
    )    
  },
)
```

This is of course only a very basic example; you'll need to set the [inset](https://typst.app/docs/reference/layout/grid/#parameters-inset) so that the line does not overlap the text, and the [page counter](https://typst.app/docs/reference/introspection/counter/#page-counter) for the page number.
